Tasks should have a function to tween, or interpolate, between two values more easily than the code sample below.

``` d
auto startTime = Time.totalTime;
auto dur = 100.msecs;
scheduleTimedTask(
{
    Game.grid.getTileByID( position ).transform.scale = 
        interp( shared vec3( TILE_SIZE / 3 ), shared vec3( TILE_SIZE / 2 ), 
            ( Time.totalTime - startTime ) / dur.toSeconds );
}, dur );
```

Instead of making programmers handle converting deltaTime to something usable, the engine should do the conversion. There should be another way to surface the current method if game programmers want it, but the default should be the obvious and expected result.

Current:

``` d
Time.deltaTime.total!"msecs"();
Time.deltaTime.fracSec.msecs;
```

New:

``` d
Time.deltaTime;
```
